    "recap_text": "CINCINNATI\n- Xavier baseball dropped a midweek match-up to Ohio State, 8-4, in 10 innings at Hayden Field on Wednesday. The loss evened the season series at 1-1.\nThe Musketeers moved to 6-16 on the year, while the Buckeyes moved to 7-12.\nOhio State picked up a run in the first and a pair in the second to take a 3-0 lead into the bottom of two. The Musketeers picked up three runs on three hits in the second to even the score.\nJonathan Fitz\nled off the inning with a walk and moved to second on a single from\nLuke Hammond\n. A double from\nPeter Johnson\nbrought Fitz home, and Hammond scored on a ground ball from Canterberry.\nCarter Christenson\ndoubled to left to bring in Johnson to tie the score at 3-3.\nXavier moved in front in the fifth after Christenson got on with a single, moved to second on a wild pitch and came home on single from\nJorge Valdes\nto lead 4-3. Ohio State scored in the sixth to make it 4-4, with the tie holding through the ninth to force extra innings.\nThe Buckeyes scored four in the top of the 10th and the Musketeers were unable to counter in the bottom of the frame to set the final score at 8-4.\nThe Musketeers remain at home for a three-game series with Wofford this weekend, set to get underway on Friday, March 20, at 3:00 p.m. and run through Sunday. All three games will be streamed on ESPN+.\nAT THE PLATE\nCarter Christenson\nwent 3-4 with a double, driving in an RBI and scoring a run.\nPeter Johnson\nrecorded a hit (1-4) a double, drove in an RBI and came around to score.\nJorge Valdes\n(1-5) drove in an RBI with a single.\nDonavan Canterberry\nfinished with an RBI.\nLuke Hammond\nwent 2-4 with a run scored.\nJonathan Fitz\ngot on with a walk and scored a run.\nClay Burdette\nalso got aboard with a walk.\non the mound\nEvan Vasiliou\nmade the start, going 5.0 innings with three runs allowed on four hits and two walks, striking out four, a season high.\nJoey Arend\nentered in the sixth walking one, and allowing one run.\nJoey Young\nentered with two on and one out in the sixth, walking one and striking out one.\nGarrett Helsel\nentered with the bases loaded and two outs in the sixth, going 1.0 innings without allowing a run or a hit. Helsel\u00a0walked three and finished with one strikeout.\nOwen Poole\nentered with the bases loaded and two outs in the seventh, going 2.2 innings with four runs allowed on one hit and one walk, striking out a pair.\nTrevor Geddes\ncame in with bases loaded and one out in the 10th, facing three batters. He allowed two hits and one walk.\nJake Hooker\nentered with the bases loaded and one out, getting the Musketeers out of the inning with a double play.\nHIGHLIGHTS"
